<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" style="color: #7B2D8E;">After Your Appointment</h3>

<div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg mb-8">
  <p class="mb-4">
    Waxing can leave your skin feeling sensitive and irritated. It's also common to see small bumps form on the skin. It's important to know that your skin is more sensitive to bacteria after waxing. Stay away from standing water to prevent complications, including swimming pools, beaches, lakes, and hot tubs.
  </p>
  <p class="mb-4">
    You should also avoid working out since sweat can irritate the area. Wear loose clothes to prevent friction and wait at least 24 hours to have sex. We recommend using a soothing gel or lotion to help the area heal. You should also exfoliate two days after the appointment to prevent ingrown hairs.
  </p>
</div>

<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: #7B2D8E;">Aftercare Instructions</h2>

